{
  "text": "Turbulence is initialized by forcing the low-wavenumber power spectra at various p 0 to an appropriate form via a linear scheme suggested by [CITATION_1] and for the parameters summarized in Table 1 . The parameter space has been designed to investigate Reynolds number regimes where existing models poorly calibrate and a range of p 0 observed in geophysical and engineering flows.",
  "correct_citation": {
    "[CITATION_1]": "120786829"
